2026-05-20| Check if Pair Product Equals Target

	Question
Return true if such a pair exists.
	Key Insight
For every number x:
		needed value =
				target / x
If that needed value already exists,
then pair found.
Need careful handling for:
		x = 0
	Approach
1.	Use hash set to store visited elements  
2.	Traverse array:
		for current x:
3.	If x == 0:
		product can only be 0
4.	Otherwise:
		if target % x == 0:
				check whether
				target/x exists in set
5.	If found:
		return true
6.	Insert current number into set
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isProduct(vector<int>& arr, long long target) {
        unordered_set<long long> st;
        for(long long x : arr){
            if(x == 0){
                if(target == 0 && st.count(0))
                    return true;
            }
            else{
                if(target % x == 0){
                    long long need = target / x;
                    if(st.count(need))
                        return true;
                }
            }
            st.insert(x);
        }
        return false;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Instead of checking all pairs:
		transform product condition into:
				search for required complement value  
Hashing reduces:
		O(n²) → O(n).
